Ri did not mention plans for the second summit between Kim and Trump that had been referred to by the U.S. leader at the United Nations earlier this week.
Instead, the minister highlighted the three meetings between Kim and South Korean leader Moon Jae-in over the past five months, adding: “If the party interested in this issue were South Korea and not the United States, the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula would not have reached this deadlock.”
