And now a page of our Almanach "Sunday Morning": On September 30, 1882, today is 136 years old and continues to count ...born in Germany the future physical Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger.
Geiger developed a method for detecting and measuring radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the device known as the Geiger counter.
