Man: "What the hell is this?"
Rogers: "It's a Geiger counter, used to locate radioactive minerals like uranium.
When we put these headphones on, we can even hear the effects of the atoms released by radioactivity in the minerals.”
Evans: "Look, it's really cracking right now!"
"Hans" Geiger died in 1945, a few days before his 63rd birthday.
