“With the support of the UK government, donors, national governments and global citizens like all of us, we can make the social injustice of malnutrition a footnote of history,” said Tracey Ullman, The Power of Nutrition’s ambassador, to a crowd at a live concert in London in April 2018.
The group also said that after more than 5,000 actions on the UK to improve mother and child nutrition, the government announced that it would fund a project, the Power of Nutrition, which will cover 5 million women and children, with interventions at the level of nutrition.
In response to one of the site’s frequently asked questions, “What makes you think we can eradicate extreme poverty?”
The Global Citizen replies: “It was a long and tortuous journey – sometimes we fell and failed.
But just like the great civil rights and anti-apartheid movements that preceded us, because we are more powerful together.
